'''Irene Miracle''' (born January 24, 1954 in [[Stillwater, Oklahoma|Stillwater]], [[Oklahoma]]) is an [[United States|American]] film and television [[actress]] and director.
==Early life== Irene Miracle was born in [[Stillwater, Oklahoma|Stillwater]], [[Oklahoma]] and is of [[Scots-Irish]], [[Russian people|Russian]], [[French people|French]] and [[Osage Nation|Osage]] descent.<ref>[http://www.changelingthemovie.net/ChangelingTheMovie/IreneMiracle/ IRENE MIRACLE]</ref>
===Acting career=== Her first film appearance was as a murder victim in ''[[L'ultimo treno della notte|Night Train Murders]]'' (1975), an [[Cinema of Italy|Italian]] ''[[The Last House on the Left (1972 film)|Last House on the Left]]''-clone. Her most prestigious role was in [[Alan Parker]]'s ''[[Midnight Express (film)|Midnight Express]]'' (1978), a worldwide [[box office]] success. For her role as the girlfriend of the incarcerated protagonist, she won the [[Golden Globe Award]] for New Star of the Year - Female.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://movies2.nytimes.com/gst/movies/filmography.html?p_id=49543 |title=Irene Miracle|accessdate=2007-01-18|first=Manohla|last=Dargis|work=The New York Times}}</ref> Miracle followed that film with another major role in [[Dario Argento]]'s ''[[Inferno (1980 film)|Inferno]]'' (1980), as a woman who comes to believe the [[New York City]] apartment building she lives in also houses a centuries-old [[witch]]. Since then, she has continued her acting work, while also writing, directing and producing.
===Directing career=== In 2009, Miracle wrote and directed the short drama film ''Changeling (aka Dawnland)''.<ref>[http://www.dawnland-movie.com/ Dawnland - Movie]</ref> In August, 2010, Miracle is set to direct ''The Baggage Claim'', a 20 minute short [[romantic fantasy film]] starring [[Coralina Cataldi-Tassoni]] and [[Tom Savini]], who also created the [[special effects]] for the film.<ref>[http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/37733/tom-savini-checkin-terror-tickets-the-baggage-claim Tom Savini Checkin' Terror Tickets at The Baggage Claim]</ref>
